13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 19 O.S. 2021, Section 215.5, is
13
14 amended to read as follows:
14
15 Section 215.5. The district attorney or his or her assistants
15
16 shall give opinion and advice to the board of county commissioners
16
17 and other civil officers of his or her counties when requested by
17
18 such officers and boards, upon all matters in which any of the
18
19 counties of his or her district are interested, or relating to the
19
20 duties of such boards or officers in which the state or counties may
20
21 have an interest. The provisions of this section shall include the
